article.headline: Cal Poly-SLO 52, Northwestern St. 18
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. -- Jonathan Daily threw for 224 yards and accounted for four touchdowns and James Noble ran for 118 yards on eight carries and a score to help Cal Poly beat Northwestern State 52-18 on Saturday night. Cal Poly (2-1) took a 14-0 lead in the first quarter when Daily scored on a 2-yard run and threw a 4-yard touchdown to Ramses Barden, who finished with nine catches for 176 yards. Daily also ran for 33 yards on six carries. Byron Lawrence scored on a 5-yard run to cut the lead to 14-7, but Northwestern State (2-2) couldn't draw closer. Daily connected with Tredale Tolver for a 45-yard touchdown and Noble scored on a 33-yard run to push Cal Poly's lead to 28-7 in the second quarter. Ryan Mole, who had 51 yards on eight carries, scored on a 4-yard run in the third for Cal Poly. John Hundley, who completed 13-of-30 passes, threw for 213 yards and a touchdown for Northwestern State. Byron Lawrence ran for 62 yards on 11 carries.
